<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-695-445  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 695 445.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Business Week  Dec 24 1990 n3193 pIS 29(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sirti: installing telecommunications for the Europe of tomorrow.andO;(Italy 1990) (Italian telecommunications installer)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Italian telecommunications installation company Sirti isinvolved in implementing a nationwide fiber-optic network which ispart of a plan called the Eighties Project.andP;  The company isupgrading switching and transmission infrastructures whilepreparing for network digitization.andP;  Sirti is installingfiber-optic lines across mountainous regions and is also layingsubmarine lines to connect Sicily, Sardinia, and the mainland.andO;Sirti is in the process of replacing the traditional coppertelephone terminal connections with fiber optical ones in manyItalian cities.andP;  Olivetti SpA and Sirti operate a joint venturecalled Eurolan which develops local area networks.andP;  Sirti and itsSpanish company SEIRT recently bought a Portuguese company whichwill enable Sirti to cover all of the Iberian peninsula.andP;  Sirtialso specializes in network management systems and developscustomized software.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sirti S.p.A. (Planning).andO;Topic:     Fiber OpticsCommunications EquipmentNetwork ManagementLocal Area Networks.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>